One day I'll tell you why she's crying.
But not today.
Today she accepts- a quiet nod to okayness-a peaceful place for all her many parts.
She yearns for something more.
Greater than herself.
In a world where everyone was silent she felt like shouting from the rooftops. Now that everyone's screaming she turns and says: there is no need,  deeper beauty lies in silence.
Being different, alien, always felt alone but so much worse than succumbing to all the sameness.

One day I'll tell you why she cries.
But not today.

A fleeting thought.
A rushed plan.
We're booking a room and suddenly everyone is stuffing random items into zippable bags.
Food!
Lots of it. 
Actually an entire case dedicated to bags of chips, frozen meats, tradition soups and twizzlers. 
A drive.
Winding and beautiful but also nauseates half the crew. 
And suddenly it's time to unload.
Coats and bags flying. Everybody's walking down excited hallways while simultaneously needing to pee üëÖ
.
The fighting never stops. Tiny arguments arise in every elevator (I mean WHO GETS TO CLICK THE BUTTON!?!?) Little bickering happens while pool splashing or choosing what we will do first. 
But the main thing is: we are together on a family adventure.
That's all there is to it.
I think its easy to lose sight- feel like it needs to be grander than....more and more topping each previous experience or really whatever the OTHER families are doing on the 'gram- but rly. It's just abt experiencing something NEW together ‚ô°

üåäANTHEM FOR THE AGESüí¶

Powerful cascading waters of turquoise split down the middle. The Jews step forth braving the fresh mud on the sea floor. It's wonderous, it's breathtaking, it's a miracle unlike any other.
With shining eyes they emerge on the other side, Miriam, brandishing her tambourine leads the women in line where they break out in joyous song.
üíô

This story makes me feel connected.  It's a link in my history that binds me on a cellular level- you see, I would be that woman (maybe the purple one?üòÇ) delighted, raising my voice in prayer and praise for the thing I've been longing for has come to fruition. üíô

Sometimes, in the religious world I come from, it feels like so many natural and beautiful things are treated perversely. But here we have it- holy women raising their voices. Dancing feet kicking in the hot white sand- faithful, holy, and would you BELIEVE IT *gasp* WITHOUT A MECHITZA?!?!
.

Dear God,
Today I pray.
I pray for HOPE, 
the promise of light at the end of a very long tunnel, and the unwavering belief that you are here- Among us.
I pray for HEALING,
soothing our crying souls, the mending of this broken world, and the miracle of a battered body brought back to life.
I pray for L‚ô°VE,
The spreading of joyous news, acceptance within our tribe, brothers and sisters of all backgrounds- one faith- standing together with pride- a unity which we need now more then ever.

Pray with me.
Know that you are heard.
Close your eyes and just be RIGHT HERE for a moment because God listens.

The fear. That horrible unrelenting shakiness that has invaded- unwilling to leave. It rushes through me in waves...the footage of hate crimes replay in my mind on constant  ugly loop. My conclusion: being a jew in America #2019 is so terribly scary.
.
SOme days it even feels like God dropped the ball. Just like WHY. how are these things allowed to happen? Isn't he watching over us? Doesn't he care for every single one of us?
.
He does.
He rly rly DOES.
Noticing God WITHIN tragedy can help us fight the FEAR. The fear that is cast when a hate crime is successful. Terrorists stepping forth brandishing a blade KNOW full well they wont hurt THOUSANDS before being apprehended but their goal is to instill FEAR in THOUSANDS. .
Noticing God is relying on God: and trusting a higher power will help us get through these tough days ahead.
.
Last night jewish men were stabbed in their Rebbes house. A place of joy, menorah lighting, &blessing turnt screams, pain & jewish blood on the floor.

One man was  terribly injured. He is STILL in  critical care.
YEHOSEF BEN PEREL 
He is the father in law of my good friend  @suryneuman
Her husb sits in that very same room, weekly. Next  to his dad, singing, talking, just being among the other congregants, every Saturday night.

Last night I made plans.
Rediculous plans. Chic flick plans that the guys weren't even interested in but decided to join anyway. I almost broke them multiple times. I heard myself saying I'd go when the back of my brain yelled "you arent even in the mood stop saying yes". And then....I DIDNT end up going- Mo and I got to the theater ten minutes too late, the movie sold out and we LITERALLY turned around and went home. You know who was in the movie tho? Sury and her husband. 
Weirdly.
But he was spared. .
God watches. And protects. And LIVES among us. Take this teeny tiny piece of comfort and hold your head higher.  Don't let those Jewish values fall to the wayside. In fact HOLD EM TIGHTER.
.
May all the inspiration and goodness gleaned from this post yield merit for the speedy recovery and well being of YEHOSEF BEN PEREL -he needs a miracle! Please stop for a moment and say even just ONE prayer in his name.

‚ô°CONFETTI IN PARTS‚ô°
I had a thought today.
A strange one. 
It's never occurred to me but I want to be a Russian Doll when I grow up! You feel me!? NO? NEVER had that thought?üòÇ so it's just me?! Lol.
I guess what I'm saying is #IFS therapy has brought out the Russian doll feels. #internalfamilysystems
is changing my life. It's a process where all my parts are spoken to, cared for and understood. "Being too aware" is a curse I've always said: >it's HARD being acutely in tune with conflicting emotions within. IFS is helping me separate those those parts and UNDERSTAND- not just be painfully receptive.

Heres the Russian Doll Dream:
One day I'll sit with my thoughts...I'll be quiet and still. My mind people wont shout or scream or panic or even cry. We'll all just sit togetherness enveloping us like a hug- calm, happy, and whole. The kind of whole a Russian doll feels when shes been tucked tight all her pieces snuggled together- in their right places- smiling internally.
How perfect does that sound?
So yeh....my goals have currently been replaced with a wooden rosey cheeked smiling toy wearing a babushka.üôä #challelujahüåπ #shabbatshalom #confetti_in_parts

‚Ä¢CONFETTI IN PARTS‚Ä¢
Sometimes I sit in front of a blank white post...the faded font reads "write caption". The curser blinking, staring as I try to put words to feelings. 
There's always SOMETHING I want to say: my desire to express freely is usually over-ridden by a part of me that would only like eloquence released. I tell that part "I understand you and it's ok!" The proof of okayness being the amount of typos and inability to spell and you guys still stay and enjoy ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èüòÇ *mind boggling* 
That part of me- who I've named "the perfectionist"- scoffs disbelieving. She is afraid of being unliked, unloved for her plain-ness. She tells me to stay relevant and interesting is to stay afloat. 
I'm thinking I disagree. I understand and yet I see my reality so fulfilled by daily things that occur OFF the gram. Lately I've been making efforts to notice that differentiation. Seeing myself in parts actually helps me to see my reality in parts....and it makes me understand just how small the Instagram part really is.
#inmymind #internalfamilysystems  #confetti_in_parts #shabbatshalom #challelujahüåπ
